@matzf: Thank you very much for your feedback and your suggestion!
I have adjusted the draft accordingly.
Best, Corine

```suggestion
## Ceremony Process {#ceremonyprocess}
```

@oncilla @knmeynell I now integrated the ASN.1 modules into the draft's appendix. This required a general headings  overhaul  in sections  `2.  Certificate Specification` and section `3.  Trust Root Configuration Specification`. It also required quite some  rewording. I believe the draft structure is overall more clear now. Please let me know if it looks ok to you. Could you 4 eye check that the new text is correct, and that I did not miss/confuse anything?

I leave some comments in GitHub where I have some remarks/questions

To better see the final result, you may want to look at the compiled [diff with main](https://author-tools.ietf.org/api/iddiff?url_1=https://scionassociation.github.io/scion-cppki_I-D/draft-dekater-scion-pki.txt&url_2=https://scionassociation.github.io/scion-cppki_I-D/asn-1/draft-dekater-scion-pki.txt) and  [HTML version](https://scionassociation.github.io/scion-cppki_I-D/asn-1/draft-dekater-scion-pki.html#name-extkeyusage-extension).

@oncilla this used to be:
```
       certificates       SEQUENCE OF Certificate }
```
Where Certificate was imported from the standard PKIX1Explicit88 module, which probably does not know how to parse SCION - specifica parts of certificates. 

For now, I used raw bytes (`ANY`) to get it working, but I think the correct way would be to have an ASN.1 module for SCION certificates, which is the second part of this PR yet to be worked on :)

