@oncilla this does not seem to be true for the initial TRC of SSUN, which has 0 votes: 
```
    votes: votes ::= {
    }
```

 Shall we change it to: 
```suggestion
       votes         SEQUENCE SIZE (0..255) OF INTEGER,
```

@oncilla  do we already have an  OID for this TRCs module? I don't think we do, right? 

If not, we need to determine the right OID. The current module assumes that we get an OID from the "SMI Security for PKIX Module Identifier" IANA registry (1.3.6.1.5.5.7.0), whose allocation policy according to RFC 7299 is of "Specification Required". However, the RFC says "The expert is expected to ensure that any new values are strongly related to the work that was done by the PKIX Working Group.", so I'm not sure if we would qualify. We could check with our ISE reviewer Russ who is also one of the two IANA experts for this registry.

Another option is to use an OID under the SCION PEN, which would not require any IANA approval:



```suggestion
   SCION-CP-PKI-TRC { 
       iso(1) identified-organization(3) dod(6) internet(1) private(4) 
       enterprise(1) scion(55324) module(0) trc(1)
   }
```

What do you think is best? I could also ask Russ, but if I were to upload a new draft version, I would first start with our own PEN, and then nicely ask if we can use something else..
